	-------------
	Related Links
	-------------

    * {{{http://www.dgs.monash.edu.au/~jwb/Japanese.html}Jim Breen's Japanese Page}} has
      lots of interesting links. He is the author of several tools on which
      JGloss is based and is the iniator of EDICT and KANJIDIC.

    * The {{{http://chasen-legacy.sourceforge.jp/}ChaSen morphological analysis tool}}
      can be used by JGloss to parse Japanese text. Download it from its
      {{{http://sourceforge.jp/projects/chasen-legacy/releases/}project page}}.

    * {{{http://www.csse.monash.edu.au/~jwb/cgi-bin/wwwjdic.cgi}Online search in EDICT 
      dictionaries}}.

    * The {{{http://www.wadoku.de/}Wadoku Jiten}} page offers online search in the Japanese-German dictionary.
      You can also help improving the dictionary there.

    * Two WWW interfaces which provide glosses for any Japanese web page without having to
      run an extra program:
      Todd Rudick's {{{http://www.rikai.com/}RIKAI server}}
      and Jim Breen's {{{http://www.csse.monash.edu.au/~jwb/cgi-bin/wwwjdic.cgi?9T}WWWJDIC}}.

    * {{{https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=sk.baka.aedict}aedict}} is an 
      open source Japanese dictionary app for Android ({{{http://code.google.com/p/aedict/}project page}}). 

    * The {{{http://www.aozora.gr.jp/}Blue Sky Collection}} is an online archive of free
      Japanese texts.

    * A {{{https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/html-ruby/}Ruby extension}} for 
      {{{http://www.mozilla.org/products/firefox/}Firefox}} enables
      the display of ruby in the browser.

